records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information charging  misdemeanor possess THC, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(e) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   No contest plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA follow up;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
4) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Minutes.
